# Rewrite Porting Order

Mandatory sequence for kernel and subgraph ports. Complements `rewrite-buffer-contract.mdc` (wiring) and `rewrite-testing.mdc` (verification).

## Phase 0 — Infrastructure

Host + harness only; golden parity optional.

- Catch2 harness + `nlrc_vksplat_gpu` minimal substrate (`rewrite-testing.mdc`)
- Headless Vulkan device, queues (`src/gpu/headless_context.hpp`)
- `StorageBuffer`, `ComputePipeline` (`src/gpu/`); ref-parity `executeCompute` / full pipeline wrapper — follow-on Phase 0
- Shader embed CMake path (`shader-build-embed.mdc`)
- Config header + generator (`nlrc_vksplat_config.hpp`, `VKSPLAT_*`, emulate flags)

## Phase 1 — Subgraph D

| Order | Kernel | Why |
|-------|--------|-----|
| 1 | `cumsum_*` | A tile indexing, `where`, E/F prune |
| 2 | `sum` | Densification sizing |
| 3 | `where` | Compaction |

## Phase 2 — Radix sort

`radix_sort/*.comp`: `upsweep` → `spine` → `downsweep` as one unit. Port before Subgraph A integration. Re-run on `ohos-debug` when available (`ref/docs/ohos-maleoon910-porting-report.md`).

## Phase 3 — Subgraph A

| Order | Kernel |
|-------|--------|
| 1 | `projection_forward` |
| 2 | `generate_keys` |
| 3 | `compute_tile_ranges` |
| 4 | `rasterize_forward` |

**Gate:** wire `forward()` only after all four pass isolated tests. Do not start Subgraph B until this gate passes.

## Phase 4 — Subgraph B

`ssim_forward`, `ssim_backward`

## Phase 5 — Subgraph C

`rasterize_backward_*` (all ref scheduler variants), then `fused_projection_backward_optimizer`

## Phase 6 — Subgraph G

Morton kernels (required before E end-of-step reorder)

## Phase 7 — Subgraph E (default ADC)

`default_*` chain per `shader-pipeline.md`; reuses D + G

## Phase 8 — Subgraph F (MCMC)

**Deferred** until Phase 7 is complete and integrated. Do not interleave E/F porting.

## Phase 9 — E2E smoke

Tiny scene, loss trend — see `rewrite-testing.mdc`

## Rules

- Fixture-first + binding contract at every kernel
- Do not wire `train_step` until Phases 3–7 gates pass
- Do not skip Phases 1–2 to test rasterize first
- Mark stages done using SPIR-V names from shader-pipeline shader index

## Deferred (Phase 2 scope)

Python bindings, viewer, perf scheduler; Thompson scheduling optimization (port all backward variants ref exposes first)
